The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, Nov. 30: Rabo India Finance Pvt Ltd today said it has acquired a 3.08 per cent stake in Dabur India Ltd. Rabo told National Stock Exchange that it has acquired 88.23 lakh shares aggregating to 3.08 per cent of the total paid-up capital of Dabur. It has bought the shares by way of pledge and, with this acquisition, Rabo?s stake in Dabur has gone up to 6.59 per cent.

 Mumbai, Nov. 30: Nirma Ltd will split its equity shares in the 1:2 ratio. Shareholders have approved the split at the EGM. Every Nirma shareholder with one share of Rs 10 fully paid up will get two shares of Rs 5 each fully paid up, Nirma told the BSE.

 New Delhi, Nov. 30: The government will take a final decision on restructuring and modernisation of Delhi and Mumbai airports only after the empowered group of ministers meet next week, said civil aviation minister Praful Patel.

 New Delhi, Nov. 30: Air Sahara today announced the launch of its Delhi-London flight from January 6 with a promotional package of a free return ticket on its domestic network or a to-and-fro trip to Singapore.

 Chandigarh, Nov. 30: Samsung Telecommunications will set up a $15-million mobile handset manufacturing facility in Haryana.




